    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "TWA\nN731TW\n707\n3 0000000000000009",
      "TWA-TRANS WORLD AIRLINES\nBoeing 707\nThe 707 ushered TWA into the jet age in 1959, and eventual-\nly flew virtually all of the carrier s routes. During the follow-.\ning 25 calendar years, TWA operated 127 707's, including\neight different models, from this early model 131 with trans-\ncontinental range, to the advanced 331B which operated the\nlong.nonstop polar flights. Although N731 TW was the first\nto be painted in TWA colors, it initially flew in the airplane's\ncertification program and became the eleventh to be deli-\nvered to the airline, on July 9, 1959. Trans World's last 707\nwas retired on October 31, 1983.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nB-047\n84564-D\npost card\nPhoto courtesy of Trans World Airlines\nN731 TW C/N 17658\n2002, 113, 480"
    ],
